def replace_all_letters(text,subject,replace_with):
    return text.replace(subject, replace_with)

Write a function called replace_all_letters(text, letter, substitute) that takes three parameters as follows:
Parameters:
 
  text: a nonempty string representing some text
  letter: a string representing a single letter to be substituted in the text
  substitute: a string representing a single letter to substitute the letter parameter
 
The function returns:
 
  A string containing the original text with ALL occurrences of letter replaced
  by the substitute.

Example:
  Arguments:
      text: "Mas sabe el diablo por viejo que por diablo"
      letter: " " (a space)
      substitute: "_" (an underscore)
  Returns:
      'Mas_sabe_el_diablo_por_viejo_que_por_diablo'
